The President of the United States, along with his senior staff, met with leaders from the faith community to discuss the need for comprehensive immigration reform. The President expressed his commitment to working with Congress in a bipartisan manner to pass a commonsense immigration reform bill. The leaders shared their concerns about the impact of the broken immigration system on families in their congregations. They discussed the pillars of reform, including a pathway to earned citizenship, cracking down on employers who exploit workers, strengthening border security, and improving the legal immigration system. The President acknowledged the progress being made by a bipartisan group in the Senate and urged the leaders to continue prioritizing the issue. The leaders agreed that the diversity of faith communities represented at the meeting demonstrated the growing consensus in America for fixing the immigration system. They thanked the President for his leadership and agreed to continue working together to advance the immigration debate in Congress.